message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - This paper involves the use of deep neural networks for image segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of coordination-guided convolutional layers is a novel approach that involves the use of positional information, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The application of this method is in medical imaging, specifically in the segmentation of pulmonary lobes, which could fall under medical imaging (cs.MED) or neural networks (cs.NEURON).
